'''''Trisopterus capelanus''''' is a fish species belonging to the cod family ([[Gadidae]]). It is found in the [[Mediterranean Sea]].<ref name=Delling>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1111/j.1095-8649.2011.03107.x| pmid = 22026604| title = Taxonomic review of the genus ''Trisopterus'' (Teleostei: Gadidae) with recognition of the capelan ''Trisopterus capelanus'' as a valid species| journal = Journal of Fish Biology| volume = 79| issue = 5| pages = 1236–1260| year = 2011| last1 = Delling | first1 = B.| last2 = Noren | first2 = M.| last3 = Kullander | first3 = S. O.| last4 = González | first4 = J. A.}}</ref><ref name=FishBase>{{FishBase genus |genus = Trisopterus|species=capelanus |month = February |year = 2014}}</ref>

The taxonomic status of ''Trisopterus capelanus'' has until recently been unclear, and it has been mostly considered to be a subspecies of ''[[Trisopterus minutus]]''. However, genetic<ref name=Delling/><ref name=Gonzalez/> and morphometric<ref name=Delling/> analyses clearly support the status of ''Trisopterus capelanus'' as a separate species. In fact, ''Trisopterus capelanus'' is more closely related to ''[[Trisopterus luscus]]'' than to ''T. minutus''.<ref name=Delling/><ref name=Gonzalez>{{Cite journal | doi = 10.1016/j.ympev.2011.11.032| title = Evolutionary history of the genus ''Trisopterus''| journal = Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution| volume = 62| issue = 3| pages = 1013–1018| year = 2012| last1 = Gonzalez | first1 = E. G. | last2 = Cunha | first2 = R. L. | last3 = Sevilla | first3 = R. G. | last4 = Ghanavi | first4 = H. R. | last5 = Krey | first5 = G. | last6 = Bautista | first6 = J. M. | pmid=22178361}}</ref>

The [[neotype]] of ''Trisopterus capelanus'' is {{convert|21|cm|abbr=on}} in [[Fish measurement|standard length]] and {{convert|23|cm|abbr=on}} in [[Fish measurement|total length]].<ref name=Delling/>

